                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/hist-357" class="program-course-title">
              HIST 357 Religion and Canadian Society in Historical Perspective (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-27550" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: History and Classical Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      History              : This course explores religious history of French and English Canada. The growth of various denominations, popular religion, Church/State relations, sectarian education, Protestant and Catholic cultures, missions among the Natives, forces of secularization. A reading knowledge of French is recommended.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        John Zucchi (Fall)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Prerequisite: HIST 202 and HIST 203 </li>
              <li>Restriction: Not open to students who have taken 101-469</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

